# ThreadSanitizer suppressions for the sanitizer-soak workflow.
#
# SwiftNIO ByteBuffer copy-on-write: the recv-buffer reuse path checks
# `isKnownUniquelyReferenced` and reallocates in place when the last other
# reference was released on a different event loop moments earlier. Swift's
# retain/release are not TSan-visible synchronization, so TSan pairs the
# releasing thread's final read with the reallocating thread's write and
# reports a race that the CoW protocol actually forbids. Every report in
# this class shows only NIO-internal frames (ByteBuffer._Storage /
# NIOPooledRecvBufferAllocator / PendingStreamWritesManager) on both sides.
#
# Keep entries narrowly scoped to the NIO storage internals so genuine
# races in ProxyKernel code (which carry our own frames) still fail the job.
race:ByteBuffer._Storage.reallocStorage
race:ByteBuffer._Storage.allocateStorage
race:ByteBuffer._slicedStorageBuffer
